This paper is about a deep learning approach for image deraining, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on designing a lightweight network, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Gaussian-Laplacian image pyramid decomposition technology may also suggest relevance to neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential value of the proposed method for other low- and high-level vision tasks, which may suggest relevance to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
